Here's how to make your NPC patrol between waypoints:

**Simple Patrol Behavior:**
```
behaviors: [
  {
    name: "patrol",
    trigger: "idle",
    actions: [
      {
        move: {
          path: ["waypoint_a", "waypoint_b", "waypoint_c"],
          speed: 2,
          loop: true
        }
      },
      { animate: "walk" }
    ]
  }
]
```

**Define Waypoints in Your Scene:**
```
scene("MyScene", {
  objects: [
    {
      type: "waypoint",
      id: "waypoint_a",
      position: { x: 0, y: 0, z: 0 }
    },
    {
      type: "waypoint",
      id: "waypoint_b",
      position: { x: 10, y: 0, z: 0 }
    },
    {
      type: "waypoint",
      id: "waypoint_c",
      position: { x: 10, y: 0, z: 10 }
    }
  ]
})
```

**Movement Options:**
- `speed: 2` - Movement speed (units per second)
- `loop: true` - Repeat the path endlessly
- `pingpong: true` - Go back and forth
- `pauseTime: 3` - Wait at each waypoint (seconds)

**Pro Tip:** Add a behavior to stop patrolling when the player is near:
```
{
  name: "greet_player",
  trigger: "player_near",
  condition: player.distance < 5,
  priority: 1,  // Higher priority interrupts patrol
  actions: [
    { face: player.position },
    { animate: "wave" }
  ]
}
```

Here's a simple combat enemy:

**Basic Enemy NPC:**
```
npc("Goblin", {
  type: "enemy",
  model: "goblin_warrior",
  geometry: { type: "humanoid", height: 1.2, width: 0.4, depth: 0.3 },
  material: { skinColor: "#6b8e23", armor: { color: "#8b4513" } },
  scale: { x: 1.0, y: 1.0, z: 1.0 },
  health: 50,

  behaviors: [
    {
      name: "idle",
      trigger: "idle",
      actions: [
        { animate: "idle" }
      ]
    },
    {
      name: "chase",
      trigger: "player_near",
      condition: player.distance < 10 && player.distance > 2,
      actions: [
        { move: { target: player.position, speed: 3 } },
        { animate: "run" }
      ]
    },
    {
      name: "attack",
      trigger: "player_near",
      condition: player.distance <= 2,
      actions: [
        { face: player.position },
        { animate: "attack_slash" },
        { damage: { target: player, amount: 10 } }
      ],
      cooldown: 1.5
    }
  ]
})
```

**Key Components:**
1. `chase` behavior - Move toward player when in range
2. `attack` behavior - Attack when close enough
3. `cooldown` - Prevents attack spam
4. `condition` - Only triggers when conditions are met

**Add Loot Drops:**
```
loot: {
  table: "goblin_loot",
  guaranteed: [{ item: "gold", count: { min: 5, max: 15 } }],
  chance: [{ item: "goblin_ear", probability: 0.3 }]
}
```

Here's how to create conditional dialogue options:

**Basic Conditional Options:**
```
dialogue("merchant_greeting", {
  character: "Merchant",
  content: "Welcome to my shop!",

  options: [
    {
      text: "Show me your wares",
      action: () => openShop("merchant_shop"),
      unlocked: true  // Always available
    },
    {
      text: "I found your lost ring!",
      action: () => {
        removeItem("lost_ring");
        completeQuest("find_ring");
        triggerDialogue("merchant_thanks");
      },
      unlocked: player.hasItem("lost_ring")  // Only if player has item
    },
    {
      text: "Tell me about the secret passage",
      action: () => triggerDialogue("merchant_secret"),
      unlocked: player.reputation["merchant"] >= 50  // Reputation check
    },
    {
      text: "I'm ready for the advanced quest",
      action: () => startQuest("advanced_quest"),
      unlocked: player.level >= 20 && player.hasCompletedQuest("basic_quest")
    }
  ]
})
```

**Common Unlock Conditions:**
```
// Item check
unlocked: player.hasItem("quest_item")

// Quest progress
unlocked: player.hasQuest("active_quest")
unlocked: player.hasCompletedQuest("previous_quest")

// Level check
unlocked: player.level >= 10

// Stat check
unlocked: player.charisma >= 15

// Reputation
unlocked: player.reputation["faction"] >= 100

// Time-based
unlocked: gameTime.hour >= 20  // Night only

// Previous dialogue choice
unlocked: player.hasMemory("chose_peaceful_path")

// Multiple conditions
unlocked: player.level >= 10 && player.hasItem("key") && !player.hasQuest("blocked_quest")
```

**Show Different Text Based on Conditions:**
```
options: [
  {
    text: player.hasCompletedQuest("help_quest") 
      ? "Thanks again for your help!"
      : "Can you help me with something?",
    action: () => { ... }
  }
]
```

Here's how to create a quest with branching outcomes:

**Quest with Multiple Paths:**
```
quest("The Stolen Artifact", {
  giver: "Museum Curator",
  level: 15,
  type: "story",

  description: "A priceless artifact has been stolen. Find the thief and decide their fate.",

  objectives: [
    {
      id: "investigate",
      description: "Investigate the crime scene",
      type: "discover",
      target: location("museum_crime_scene")
    },
    {
      id: "find_thief",
      description: "Track down the thief",
      type: "discover",
      target: location("thief_hideout")
    },
    {
      id: "confront",
      description: "Confront the thief",
      type: "dialogue",
      target: "thief_npc"
    }
  ],

  branches: [
    {
      id: "justice",
      condition: player.choice == "turn_in",
      completeText: "You turned the thief over to the authorities.",
      rewards: {
        experience: 1000,
        gold: 500,
        reputation: { guards: 50, thieves: -100 }
      }
    },
    {
      id: "mercy",
      condition: player.choice == "let_go",
      completeText: "You let the thief go. They promised to return the artifact.",
      rewards: {
        experience: 800,
        gold: 200,
        reputation: { thieves: 50, guards: -25 },
        unlockQuest: "Thief's Gratitude"
      }
    },
    {
      id: "profit",
      condition: player.choice == "take_cut",
      completeText: "You took a cut of the profits and kept quiet.",
      rewards: {
        experience: 600,
        gold: 2000,
        reputation: { guards: -50 },
        item: { id: "stolen_gem", rarity: "rare" }
      }
    }
  ]
})
```

**The Confrontation Dialogue:**
```
dialogue("thief_confrontation", {
  character: "The Thief",
  content: "Please, I only did it to save my family! What will you do?",

  options: [
    {
      text: "You're coming with me to face justice.",
      action: () => {
        player.choice = "turn_in";
        completeQuest("The Stolen Artifact", "justice");
      }
    },
    {
      text: "Return the artifact and I'll let you go.",
      action: () => {
        player.choice = "let_go";
        completeQuest("The Stolen Artifact", "mercy");
      }
    },
    {
      text: "How about we split the profits?",
      action: () => {
        player.choice = "take_cut";
        completeQuest("The Stolen Artifact", "profit");
      },
      unlocked: player.charisma >= 14
    }
  ]
})
```

**Track Choices for Future Content:**
```
action: () => {
  addMemory("quest_stolen_artifact_choice", "mercy");
  // Future quests can check this memory
}
```

Here's how to add audio to your HoloScript scene:

**Basic Scene Audio:**
```
scene("ForestGrove", {
  environment: { ... },
  objects: [ ... ],

  audio: {
    ambient: "forest_birds_wind",
    music: "peaceful_exploration",
    volume: 0.7
  }
})
```

**Layered Ambient Audio:**
```
audio: {
  ambient: [
    { sound: "wind_light", volume: 0.5 },
    { sound: "birds_chirping", volume: 0.3 },
    { sound: "leaves_rustling", volume: 0.4 }
  ],
  music: "forest_theme",
  volume: 0.7
}
```

**Sound Effects on Objects:**
```
objects: [
  {
    type: "interactive",
    id: "campfire",
    position: { x: 5, y: 0, z: 3 },
    audio: {
      loop: "fire_crackling",
      volume: 0.6,
      range: 10,
      falloff: "linear"
    }
  }
]
```

**Trigger Sounds in Behaviors:**
```
behaviors: [
  {
    name: "attack",
    trigger: "combat",
    actions: [
      { sound: "sword_swing" },
      { animate: "attack_slash" },
      { damage: { target: player, amount: 15 } }
    ]
  }
]
```

**Dynamic Music Changes:**
```
// In a state machine or sequence
entry: () => {
  crossfadeMusic("combat_intense", duration: 2);
}

// When combat ends
onExit: () => {
  crossfadeMusic("peaceful_exploration", duration: 3);
}
```

**Sequence Sound Effects:**
```
sequence("boss_intro", {
  events: [
    { time: 0, action: () => sound("ominous_rumble") },
    { time: 1.5, action: () => sound("boss_roar") },
    { time: 2, action: () => crossfadeMusic("boss_theme", 1) }
  ]
})
```

**Audio Properties:**
- `volume` - 0.0 to 1.0
- `range` - How far sound travels
- `falloff` - "linear", "exponential", "none"
- `loop` - For continuous sounds
- `spatialize` - 3D positioning (true/false)

Here's how to add particle effects to abilities:

**Ability with Particles:**
```
ability("Fireball", {
  type: "spell",
  class: "mage",
  level: 5,

  stats: {
    manaCost: 50,
    cooldown: 6,
    castTime: 1.5,
    range: 20
  },

  effects: {
    // When casting starts
    cast: {
      animation: "cast_spell",
      particle: "fire_charge_hands",
      sound: "fire_charging"
    },

    // When projectile hits
    impact: {
      animation: "explosion",
      particle: "fire_explosion",
      sound: "explosion_fire",
      shake: { intensity: 0.5, duration: 0.3 }
    }
  },

  projectile: {
    model: "orb_fire",
    geometry: { type: "sphere", radius: 0.3 },
    material: {
      color: "#ff6600",
      emissive: "#ff3300",
      emissiveIntensity: 1.5
    },
    speed: 25,
    trail: "flame_trail"  // Particle trail
  }
})
```

**Custom Particle Definition:**
```
particle("fire_explosion", {
  type: "burst",
  count: 50,
  lifetime: { min: 0.5, max: 1.5 },

  emission: {
    shape: "sphere",
    radius: 0.5
  },

  properties: {
    size: { start: 0.5, end: 0.1 },
    color: {
      start: "#ff6600",
      end: "#330000"
    },
    opacity: { start: 1.0, end: 0.0 },
    speed: { min: 5, max: 15 },
    gravity: -2
  },

  texture: "particle_fire",
  blendMode: "additive"
})
```

**Continuous Particle Effect (Aura):**
```
particle("healing_aura", {
  type: "continuous",
  rate: 20,  // Particles per second
  lifetime: { min: 1, max: 2 },

  emission: {
    shape: "ring",
    radius: 3
  },

  properties: {
    size: { start: 0.2, end: 0.4 },
    color: { start: "#00ff88", end: "#ffffff" },
    speed: { min: 1, max: 3 },
    direction: "up"
  }
})
```

**Trigger Particles in Sequences:**
```
sequence("power_up", {
  events: [
    { time: 0, action: () => particle("charge_start", position: this.position) },
    { time: 1, action: () => particle("energy_spiral") },
    { time: 2, action: () => particle("power_explosion") }
  ]
})
```

**Particle Types:**
- `burst` - One-time explosion
- `continuous` - Ongoing emission
- `trail` - Follow moving object
- `ring` - Circular pattern
- `beam` - Line effect

Here's how to handle save/load in HoloScript:

**Define What to Save:**
```
saveData({
  // Player stats
  player: {
    level: player.level,
    experience: player.experience,
    health: player.health,
    mana: player.mana,
    position: player.position,
    rotation: player.rotation
  },

  // Inventory
  inventory: player.inventory,
  equipment: player.equipment,
  gold: player.gold,

  // Progress
  quests: {
    active: player.activeQuests,
    completed: player.completedQuests
  },
  achievements: player.achievements,

  // World state
  worldState: {
    npcsKilled: stats.npcsKilled,
    chestsOpened: stats.chestsOpened,
    memories: player.memories
  },

  // Preferences
  settings: {
    volume: settings.volume,
    difficulty: settings.difficulty
  },

  // Metadata
  saveTime: Date.now(),
  playTime: stats.playTime,
  version: "1.0.0"
})
```

**Auto-Save System:**
```
autoSave({
  enabled: true,
  interval: 300,  // Every 5 minutes
  slots: 3,       // Rotate between 3 auto-save slots
  triggers: [
    "quest_complete",
    "level_up",
    "zone_transition"
  ]
})
```

**Manual Save Points:**
```
interactive("save_crystal", {
  type: "save_point",
  position: { x: 0, y: 1, z: 0 },
  geometry: { type: "sphere", radius: 0.5 },
  material: { color: "#4488ff", emissive: "#2266ff", emissiveIntensity: 1 },

  action: () => {
    particle("save_effect");
    sound("save_chime");
    saveGame();
    notify("Game Saved");
  }
})
```

**Load Game:**
```
loadGame({
  onLoad: (data) => {
    // Restore player
    player.level = data.player.level;
    player.position = data.player.position;
    player.inventory = data.inventory;

    // Restore world
    restoreWorldState(data.worldState);

    // Restore quests
    player.activeQuests = data.quests.active;
    player.completedQuests = data.quests.completed;
  },

  onError: (error) => {
    notify("Failed to load save");
    console.error(error);
  }
})
```

**Save Slots UI:**
```
saveSlots({
  count: 10,
  display: [
    "characterName",
    "level",
    "playTime",
    "saveTime",
    "location"
  ],
  screenshot: true  // Capture thumbnail
})
```

**Version Migration:**
```
onLoad: (data) => {
  if (data.version == "0.9.0") {
    // Migrate old save format
    data = migrateSave_0_9_to_1_0(data);
  }
  // Apply data...
}
```
